                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="29233" author="luke" created="Mon, 21 Jan 2008 07:43:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We should also consider credentials expiry (forced change of password via AuthenticationProcessingFilter).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="31318" author="luke" created="Mon, 28 Jan 2008 03:13:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Needs more discussion on requirements so won&apos;t be in 2.0&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="38055" author="jonnio" created="Thu, 31 Jul 2008 03:23:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We had to write a custom filter that acts on the authentication object checking for a fields that contain remaning grace logins and password expiration date. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When the user gets within a few days of the expiration date we send them to the password change url. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If they are consuming grace logins, we send them to a page that says their password is expired and they should change it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="52381" author="luke" created="Wed, 24 Mar 2010 10:05:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Closing, as this is not something that is going to be added to the core project in the foreseeable future. This is more likely something that would be implemented by a separate Identity Management product with which we could integrate (cf the OpenLDAP ppolicy support).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="126608" author="issuemaster" created="Sat, 6 Feb 2016 06:34:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue has been migrated to &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-security/issues/873&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-security/issues/873&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
